The '''Rennell starling''' ('''''Aplonis insularis''''') is a species of [[starling]] in the family [[Sturnidae]]. It is [[endemic]] to [[Rennell Island]] in the [[Solomon Islands]].

The [[plumage]] of the Rennell starling is blackish with a green-blue gloss. It has a yellow-orange eye and a short tail. It is an abundant bird of tropical moist lowland [[forest]]s, secondary growth and coconut plantations.

